  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (adversarial INT-1)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). This package is a synthetic adversarial sample targeting COMPOUND-01 via simultaneous W-EP-01 (orphan claim, no prov:wasDerivedFrom on the bound Claim) and W-AL-01 (multiple ValidationResults lacking hasUncertaintyQuantification).",
